The equivalent annual cost (EAC) is the quantitative measure used to compare two projects/assets that have different lifespans. This can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{EAC}&=\dfrac{\text{Net present value}}{\text{Annuity factor}}
\end{aligned}$$

In order to solve for the net present value (NPV), we will use this formula:
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{NPV}&=\text{Initial cashflow}+\text{Present value cash flow}+\dfrac{\text{Net working capital}}{(1+\text{Expected return})^\text{times}}
\end{aligned}$$
